Here's a recursive function in Python that returns the number of elements in the given set S:

```python
def count_elements(S, index=0):
    if index == len(S):
        return 0
    return 1 + count_elements(S, index + 1)

S = [1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15]
print(count_elements(S))
```

This function takes the set S and an optional index parameter (default is 0). It checks if the index is equal to the length of the set, in which case it returns 0. Otherwise, it returns 1 plus the result of the function called with the same set and an incremented index.
